The paper proposes a method for interpretable reinforcement learning using ensemble methods, specifically boosted regression trees. This work falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves developing a new learning algorithm. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of AI. The paper also deals with robotics (cs.RO) as it discusses the application of the proposed method to robotic control problems. The use of regression trees also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
